{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-3092"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Manufacture of bicycles and invalid carriages"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "3092"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :bicycle-mobility/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:worker-safety :rider-safety :mobility-access-safety]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :bicycle-mobility-plant-operations-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :eda :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "BikeAdvisor ⊣ Bicycle & Mobility Device Plant Operations Governor,
 langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit ledger. A plant
 OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for bicycle and invalid-carriage
 (wheelchair/mobility-aid) manufacturing (frame-welding/assembly/
 test-bench lines producing finished bicycles, manual/power
 wheelchairs and mobility scooters) -- not direct welding/assembly/
 test-bench-equipment control authority and not safety-certification
 authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Twelve concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct welding/assembly/test-bench-equipment control),
 permanent equipment-actuate block, permanent safety-certification-
 authority block (this actor never self-issues an ISO 4210 / ISO 7176
 bicycle-or-wheelchair safety certification), independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-quantity recompute against the batch's own
 logged production quantity, double-schedule guard, product-category
 validation, weight-capacity plausibility validation, and weld-
 defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging
 (frame-weld-defect/brake-safety/structural-integrity) ALWAYS
 escalates to a human plant supervisor; `:log-production-batch` is
 the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
